      <idAbs>Special purpose districts have regulations that supplement and modify the underlying zoning for distinctive neighborhoods with particular issues and goals. The district designation is indicated in the SDNAME attribute. The abbreviation as shown on the zoning map is indicated in the SDLBL attribute. See also Special Purpose Subdistricts, which contains both the main special purpose district boundaries and the internal subdistricts. Subdistrict data has not been fully digitized and may be incomplete. See the Zoning Resolution for a complete description of the special purpose district. Where appropriate, the Zoning Resolution includes a district map showing subdistricts and subareas within the special purpose district.</idAbs>
